Executive Summary
Q1 performance shows a clear structural imbalance in the supply chain: high‑margin premium skincare is under-supplied in high-growth regions, while budget makeup is materially overstocked in declining markets. This is directly impacting revenue, margin, and service KPIs.

Premium skincare demand is rising in North and sharply rising in East, yet stock cover is critically low (4–5 days) with delayed supply and no confirmed replenishment. Fill rate in these regions is only 84%, well below acceptable levels for a flagship category.

At the same time, declining budget makeup and budget skincare SKUs carry 25–34 days of stock in several regions, contributing to $120,000 in excess inventory and inventory turns of only 5.4. Forecast accuracy (78%) and fragmented planning tools are compounding the issue.

The next 90 days must focus on protecting premium revenue, rebalancing inventory, tightening supplier control, and introducing differentiated stock policies by category and region.

